cs.LO, cs.GT, cs.DS, cs.FL, cs.PL

This paper deals with the synthesis of optimal strategies for resource-aware automata and games. The topic of optimal synthesis is typically studied in the area of logic and verification (cs.LO). The paper also deals with parity games, which are a type of game theory (cs.GT) and uses concepts from automata theory (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper deals with strategies for satisfying acceptance conditions, which is a topic in formal languages (cs.FL) and programming languages (cs.PL).
